.42268121,'Bernières-sur-Mer','France','1944-06-07','','',1,'2017-08-07 22:00:00','2019-01-27 19:18:41'),(44,1,'BsM06','','Troops disembarking with int the back, the Canadian House.',49.33604050,-0.42418861,'Bernières-sur-Mer','France','1944-06-06','','',1,'2007-10-31 23:00:00','2019-01-27 19:18:41'),(45,1,'BsM04','','Once the invasion got on the way, MP were directing traffic. The church in the back, was hit to make sure the enemy was not using it as an observation point.',49.33147430,-0.42381501,'Bernières-sur-Mer','France','1944-06-06','','',1,'2007-10-31 23:00:00','2019-01-27 19:18:41'),(46,1,'BsM05','Garding the first POW','Canadians are garding there first prisoners of war. You can see the bunker in the back which is still there.',49.33584976,-0.42021415,'Bernières-sur-Mer','France','1944-06-06','','',1,'2007-10-31 23:00:00','2019-01-27 19:18:41'),(47,3,'Juno02','D-Day','Mix of shots by the Hollywood irregulars. Direction given by George Stevens. Shots on the beach, shots near the old train station. Talk with the locals. British directing traffic.',49.33515167,-0.42212197,'Bernières-sur-Mer','France','1944-06-06','','',1,'2007-10-31 23:00:00','2019-01-27 19:18:41'),(48,3,'Juno01','D-Day Langing','This is more or less the spot where this footage was shot. It was shot by a fixed camera on the landing craft. This only for the purpose of intel gathering. ',49.33469391,-0.40448448,'Bernières-sur-Mer','France','1944-06-06','','',1,'2007-10-31 23:00:00','2019-01-27 19:18:41'),(49,1,'noville02','Knocked out German tank','',50.06356812,5.76066399,'Noville','Belgium','1945-01-15','','',1,'2007-10-31 23:00:00','2019-01-27 19:18:41'),(50,1,'ChalonsMarne01','','Bridge Across the Marne River in Chalons, bombed by the Germans.',48.95420074,4.35105848,'Châlons','France','1944-08-09','US Army Signal Core','',1,'2007-10-31 23:00:00','2019-01-27 19:18:41'),(51,1,'ChalonsMarne02','','Soldiers and locals crossing the bombed out bridge, just before the Allies repair it with a Baile